  "prompt": "What useful thing did you learn today?",
  "response": "Today, I learned more about how to effectively use the **SCAMPER** technique for creative problem-solving. SCAMPER is an acronym that stands for Substitute, Combine, Adapt, Modify, Put to another use, Eliminate, and Reverse/Rearrange. It\u2019s a fantastic tool for brainstorming and innovating by rethinking existing ideas or products. For example, applying \"Combine\" to a smartphone and a smartwatch could lead to new hybrid wearable tech. It\u2019s a structured way to think outside the box and generate fresh ideas! What about you\u2014did you learn something interesting today?",
